ðŸ“– How to Use 
Using the application is quite simple.


Add GitHub usernames in the main function to fetch their data:

await fetchUser('username1');
await fetchUser('username2');

Run the program, and the following outputs will appear in the console:

User details: Includes their GitHub ID, bio, number of repositories, etc.
Repository details: Shows the name, description, stars, and fork status for each repository.
Summary:
A list of all fetched users.
Total number of public repositories across all users.
Top 5 users with the most repositories.
